<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 5000i and 9000i - RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - RADIATOR AND
        COMPONENT REMOVal
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVal</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
            <title>CROSS-MEMBER</title>
            <figure id="f1200801" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200801.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="352px" scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Radiator Assembly And Connections</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RADIATOR MOUNTING BRACKETS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. COOLING SYSTEM HOSE CONNECTIONS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPES</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. CHARGE AIR COOLER PIPE CLAMPS</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. RADIATOR CORE</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>Prior to removal of cooling system components, the cooling system should be drained. Place a tray
                below radiator drain plug (petcock) and drain coolant. Save coolant for refilling system after replacing
                all components.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1200802" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g01200802.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="312px" scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Front Cross-Member</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TOW HOOK</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BUMPER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. RADIATOR SCREEN PROTECTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HINGE MOUNTING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. CROSS-MEMBER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The front cross-member must be removed to access radiator removal.</para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Beginning at the front cross-member lower flange, loosen and remove the bolts (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200803">Item 1, Figure 3</hotlnk>) securing the mesh screen protecting the lower
                    section of the radiator core (when applicable).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200803" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200803.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200803.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Lower Screen Removal (When Applicable)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. LOWER SCREEN MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After removing screen assembly, locate the cross-member mounting bolts for the front tow
                    hooks (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200802">Item 1, Figure 2</hotlnk>). Loosen and remove bolts and tow hook (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200804">Item 2, Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove bumper mounting bracket bolts located above the tow hook bolt holes. Remove the
                    bumper mounting bracket (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200802">Item 2, Figure 2</hotlnk>). Follow the same procedure to remove opposite
                    side mounting bolts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200804" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200804.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200804.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="232px"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Front Cross-member Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FRONT CROSS-MEMBER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TOW HOOK MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a pry bar (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1200805">Figure 5</hotlnk>), loosen and remove the cross-member assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1200805" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1200805.webp" filename="../figg12/G1200805.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                         scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="288px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Remove Front Cross-member</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
